# SYS-LIC-Z2
## License Lifecycle Controller

Version: 2.0

---

# Overview

SYS-LIC-Z2 serves as the lifecycle orchestration controller for the HyperSync License Operating System.

It is responsible for validating lifecycle transition requests, enforcing operational safeguards, acquiring exclusive processing ownership, and routing approved requests to the appropriate downstream controller.

Rather than directly applying every license mutation, SYS-LIC-Z2 manages the lifecycle decision process and transfers execution authority to the correct operating system while preserving complete governance evidence.

---

# Architectural Purpose

SYS-LIC-Z2 is responsible for:

• Lifecycle Transition Validation

• Processing Lock Management

• Transition Approval

• Operational Routing

• Gate Authorization Coordination

• Ownership Transfer

• Governance Evidence Generation

---

# Core Responsibilities

The controller performs the following operational sequence:

- Monitor license lifecycle requests
- Validate operational readiness
- Acquire processing lock
- Normalize lifecycle payload
- Validate transition contract
- Route approved requests
- Transfer workflow ownership
- Append immutable governance evidence

Every lifecycle request follows a deterministic execution contract before ownership is transferred.

